22/01/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Macedonian and Albanian anti-corruption panels vowed on Wednesday (21 January) to improve co-operation and regularly exchange experience in the fight against corruption.
Experts from the two institutions also agreed that a consistent legislative environment and stable political climate are the main preconditions for eliminating corruption.
In other news, Danish diplomat SÃ¸ren Jensen Petersen was selected to serve as EU Special Representative to Macedonia, effective 1 March.
He replaces Alexis Brouhns, whose mandate is expiring.
(Utrinski Vesnik - 22/01/04;
MIA, Makfax - 21/01/04)
